rComments: Very good prof. Very clear and very knowledgable.  Really can't blame him for the exams because there is A LOT to cover molecularly. Best advice, review lecture notes before class, right after class and once during that week. Then study for a week before exam.(no txt book thankfully) Its like math class: PRACTICE.

Awesome prof. Attend all classes because he repeats stuff that he wants you to know. Study the slides, and if needed, make summaries of the notes he puts together for you. Also comes in on the weekends before exams to re-explain stuff and answer questions. Should teach more neuro courses if he's not too busy.
Very good prof ... attend his lectures .... he repeats stuff again and again until its drilled in ur brain ... if u attend all classes ... therez no way u can get less than 'B'

Dr. Duffy teaches Synaptic. Excellent Excellent Excellent lecturer. Exams were unfair (even though he bell curved) - unfair in the sense that the questions did not reflect the material taught. But otherwise he is extremely helpful.
